ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: The event name for which the data was collected
A car accident in which you or another person in the car was hurt bad enough to require medical attention
Significant accident or medical condition, including coronavirus, for which you needed specialized, intensive, or painful medical treatment
Witness or caught in a fire that caused significant property damage or personal injury
Witness or caught in a natural disaster that caused significant property damage or personal injury
Witness or victim of a school shooting or other act of terrorism
Witness death or mass destruction in a war zone
Witness someone shot or stabbed in the community
Shot, stabbed, or beat badly by a non-family member
Beaten to the point of having bruises or had a more serious injury caused by a grown up in the home
Witness the grownups in the home push, shove or hit one another
A peer forced you to do something sexually
Learned about the life-threatening illness or sudden unexpected death of a loved one due to coronavirus, cancer, violence, or other cause
Was robbed and assaulted or robbed and threatened physically
